main event: On July 22, 1953, a visual observation of a Venuslike object was reported in California.
interesting points: The object exhibited erratic movement and emitted bright light,The observation lasted for 1 and a half minutes,The object moved from horizon to horizon during the observation period,The report concluded that it was likely a conventional aircraft or fireball,There are no photographs included in the report.
witness description: An aircraft service mechanic and a weather observer
